00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,661
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:45,818 --> 00:00:47,695
CHAPTER 32:
A VARIABLE CALLED NA DEUL-I

3
00:00:47,778 --> 00:00:49,947
-Everything going well?
-Mm-hmm.

4
00:00:50,030 --> 00:00:51,615
[gentle pop music playing on speaker]

5
00:00:51,699 --> 00:00:53,492
It's nice to see you're doing well too.

6
00:00:54,118 --> 00:00:55,494
[chuckles]

7
00:00:57,454 --> 00:01:00,457
Honestly I was a little surprised
to hear from you,

8
00:01:00,541 --> 00:01:01,542
but glad too.

9
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,838
Really, then
why didn't you reach out to me first?

10
00:01:07,006 --> 00:01:08,299
[chuckles]

11
00:01:10,718 --> 00:01:11,802
Are you okay now?

12
00:01:12,386 --> 00:01:13,554
Mmm.

13
00:01:13,637 --> 00:01:16,473
I was so worried
when I heard about your surgery.

14
00:01:16,557 --> 00:01:17,850
I couldn't contact you.

15
00:01:20,394 --> 00:01:21,896
I'm sorry I didn't tell you.

16
00:01:22,730 --> 00:01:24,481
I was just as shocked myself.

17
00:01:25,357 --> 00:01:26,483
And I was frustrated.

18
00:01:28,193 --> 00:01:29,987
So, you decided to become a teacher?

19
00:01:30,070 --> 00:01:31,530
That was unexpected.

20
00:01:31,614 --> 00:01:33,949
I thought you'd obviously continue
with the research.

21
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:36,201
[no audible dialogue]

22
00:01:36,285 --> 00:01:38,287
[slow, gentle music playing]

23
00:01:41,582 --> 00:01:43,334
[both chuckling]

24
00:01:43,417 --> 00:01:45,502
-What is it?
-What?

25
00:01:51,717 --> 00:01:54,053
[both chuckle]

26
00:01:56,805 --> 00:01:58,057
[E-den] Eui-ju?

27
00:01:58,557 --> 00:01:59,558
What are you doing here?

28
00:01:59,642 --> 00:02:00,976
EPISODE 10

29
00:02:01,852 --> 00:02:02,853
Mr. Ha.

30
00:02:02,937 --> 00:02:07,024
[stuttering] I just came here to study,
[chuckles] But I'm going to go home now.

31
00:02:07,107 --> 00:02:08,400
Eui-ju.

32
00:02:08,484 --> 00:02:10,945
You finally decided to start studying?

33
00:02:11,028 --> 00:02:13,238
[laughs]

34
00:02:15,074 --> 00:02:17,743
[chuckling] And how come you're here?

35
00:02:18,369 --> 00:02:20,287
-Is that Mr. Ga?
-[Eui-ju whispering] No, wait.

36
00:02:20,371 --> 00:02:22,289
Look who's here!

37
00:02:22,373 --> 00:02:25,292
The cold- blooded robot,
Mr. Ga, is having coffee with someone,

38
00:02:25,376 --> 00:02:26,835
and a lady at that!

39
00:02:26,919 --> 00:02:28,879
[stammers] Hold on.

40
00:02:29,588 --> 00:02:30,589
Are you…

41
00:02:32,132 --> 00:02:34,510
Professor Na Deul-i? Is that right?

42
00:02:35,427 --> 00:02:36,720
Uh…

43
00:02:36,804 --> 00:02:39,306
-Yes.
-[gasps, laughs]

44
00:02:39,390 --> 00:02:41,058
Oh, my! I knew it! I saw you on the news.

45
00:02:41,141 --> 00:02:44,561
I was really impressed by your interview
about winning the Fields Medal.

46
00:02:44,645 --> 00:02:46,438
[Deul-i] Oh, thank you so much.

47
00:02:46,522 --> 00:02:48,691
Oops, I'm sorry, my bad.

48
00:02:48,774 --> 00:02:50,693
Hello. I'm Mr. Ga's colleague at school.

49
00:02:50,776 --> 00:02:53,696
My name is Ha E-den.
It's so very nice to meet you.

50
00:02:54,405 --> 00:02:55,447
I see.

51
00:02:56,407 --> 00:02:57,533
Oh.

52
00:02:57,616 --> 00:02:58,742
[chuckles]

53
00:02:59,618 --> 00:03:04,081
Anyway, I was just wondering, what exactly
is your relationship with Mr. Ga Woo-su?

54
00:03:05,791 --> 00:03:07,918
-We're friends.
-Oh, yeah?

55
00:03:08,002 --> 00:03:09,962
So you're just friends? I see.

56
00:03:10,045 --> 00:03:12,047
But you're alone together
at this coffee shop.

57
00:03:12,131 --> 00:03:14,508
That seems like a date to me. [chuckles]

58
00:03:15,926 --> 00:03:16,927
Should we go?

59
00:03:17,011 --> 00:03:18,303
-[chuckles]
-Let's go.

60
00:03:18,387 --> 00:03:22,141
[sighs] The two of you make
such a lovely couple.

61
00:03:22,224 --> 00:03:24,184
Like a match made in heaven.

62
00:03:24,268 --> 00:03:25,269
See you soon.

63
00:03:25,352 --> 00:03:26,562
-[stutters] Goodbye.
-Goodbye.

64
00:03:27,604 --> 00:03:28,939
Keep studying, all right?

65
00:03:29,023 --> 00:03:31,108
If you want to become someone
like Professor Na Deul-i.

66
00:03:32,067 --> 00:03:33,110
Take care now.

67
00:03:36,947 --> 00:03:38,115
-[Woo-su] Allow me.
-[door opens]

68
00:03:38,198 --> 00:03:40,200
[Deul-i] Oh. Okay. Thank you.

69
00:03:40,284 --> 00:03:41,285
Hello there.

70
00:03:42,703 --> 00:03:44,455
Uh… My name is Yeo Eui-ju,

71
00:03:44,538 --> 00:03:47,249
and Mr. Ga Woo-su is actually
my homeroom teacher at school.

72
00:03:48,083 --> 00:03:50,461
Oh. Hello there.

73
00:03:51,170 --> 00:03:54,798
Whoa. It's such a surprise to see that
you have a student of your own.

74
00:03:54,882 --> 00:03:56,050
[chuckles]

75
00:03:56,133 --> 00:03:59,511
Are you his friend
from when you were in college?

76
00:03:59,595 --> 00:04:01,555
Oh, no.
We've been friends since middle school.

77
00:04:02,347 --> 00:04:04,183
Ah… Middle school.

78
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:06,268
That's a long time.

79
00:04:06,351 --> 00:04:07,519
You can go now.

80
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,772
Remember what I offered.

81
00:04:10,606 --> 00:04:11,690
You'll consider it?

82
00:04:13,192 --> 00:04:14,359
I'm not sure.

83
00:04:15,027 --> 00:04:17,446
Oh. Are you playing hard to get?

84
00:04:17,529 --> 00:04:19,364
[chuckles] Just get going now.

85
00:04:19,448 --> 00:04:20,532
All right.

86
00:04:20,616 --> 00:04:22,743
Oh. I'll see you again
another time, Eui-ju.

87
00:04:23,577 --> 00:04:25,329
Yes. Goodbye now.

88
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,122
Bye.

89
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:41,095
-Mr. Ga, your friend…
-[sighs]

90
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:44,056
…she seems like a really wonderful person.

91
00:04:44,139 --> 00:04:46,725
She's beautiful
and she seems really kind too.

92
00:04:47,392 --> 00:04:49,770
And to have even won a Fields Medal.

93
00:04:49,853 --> 00:04:51,563
Wow. That's seriously amazing, really.

94
00:04:51,647 --> 00:04:52,981
I wish I had a friend like that.

95
00:04:54,608 --> 00:04:56,777
I bet she's incredibly popular too.

96
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:58,362
She probably has a boyfriend.

97
00:04:59,029 --> 00:05:03,242
[sighs] But also, it could be tiring
to be around someone that perfect.

98
00:05:03,325 --> 00:05:05,077
You know,
when someone's good at everything,

99
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,287
the people around them tend
to get compared.

100
00:05:08,664 --> 00:05:10,499
It can make them feel small for no reason.

101
00:05:13,127 --> 00:05:14,128
So what's your point?

102
00:05:15,712 --> 00:05:17,840
I mean, I was just wondering

103
00:05:17,923 --> 00:05:21,552
what kind of boyfriend
someone that gorgeous might have.

104
00:05:22,177 --> 00:05:23,428
Why are you wondering?

105
00:05:25,931 --> 00:05:28,600
If you don't get over a 50
on the upcoming math exam,

106
00:05:28,684 --> 00:05:32,187
I'll tell your parents about your novel
during the parent-teacher meeting.

107
00:05:34,189 --> 00:05:35,190
Huh?

108
00:05:35,858 --> 00:05:37,317
Hey, no, that's unfair!

109
00:05:37,401 --> 00:05:40,154
Mr. Ga, you don't mean it, do you?

110
00:05:40,237 --> 00:05:41,488
Do you? You shouldn't…

111
00:05:42,614 --> 00:05:44,741
Come on, Mr. Ga.

112
00:05:45,409 --> 00:05:48,620
I'll try my best.
But I may not be able to get a 50.

113
00:05:50,539 --> 00:05:54,334
Mr. Ga, about what your friend
was talking about earlier…

114
00:05:54,418 --> 00:05:57,045
[clears throat]
What did she ask you to consider?

115
00:05:57,838 --> 00:05:59,381
It's none of your business.

116
00:06:00,048 --> 00:06:02,176
Would it kill him
to say it a little nicer?

117
00:06:02,259 --> 00:06:03,343
[phone buzzes]

118
00:06:03,886 --> 00:06:04,887
Remember my soda.

119
00:06:05,721 --> 00:06:06,930
Mr. Ga, wait a second.

120
00:06:07,556 --> 00:06:09,141
H-Hold on, wait there.

121
00:06:10,017 --> 00:06:11,643
Oh, no. Don't go, don't go, don't go.

122
00:06:11,727 --> 00:06:13,312
Uh… Just wait right there.

123
00:06:13,395 --> 00:06:14,396
I'll be right back.

124
00:06:14,479 --> 00:06:16,106
-[whimsical music playing]
-Hey, hey.

125
00:06:23,530 --> 00:06:25,115
I'm all done. [chuckles]

126
00:06:27,534 --> 00:06:29,912
Drinking soda is a common cause
of constipation.

127
00:06:30,787 --> 00:06:33,081
Hope you won't have to go to the ER again.

128
00:06:33,165 --> 00:06:36,084
I didn't buy it for me.
I had to buy it for my younger brother.

129
00:06:36,877 --> 00:06:38,212
What a sister.

130
00:06:38,295 --> 00:06:41,548
[chuckles] He just uses me
because he has dirt on me.

131
00:06:41,632 --> 00:06:43,258
-[sniffs]
-What does he have on you?

132
00:06:44,551 --> 00:06:48,347
You see. [sighs] It's just that
I only got caught by two people.

133
00:06:50,349 --> 00:06:53,936
That day,
I was lost in my writing again as usual.

134
00:06:55,729 --> 00:06:57,981
And I was also chatting online.

135
00:06:58,065 --> 00:06:59,483
[whimsical music playing]

136
00:07:01,735 --> 00:07:03,070
[online friend 1] I was just wondering

137
00:07:03,153 --> 00:07:05,280
under what name
you've all saved this group chat.

138
00:07:05,364 --> 00:07:07,199
[online friend 2] Beautiful Life. BL.

139
00:07:07,282 --> 00:07:09,326
[online friend 3] How about
a real estate group chat?

140
00:07:09,409 --> 00:07:11,119
Since my husband
checks my phone sometimes.

141
00:07:12,496 --> 00:07:14,998
[Eui-ju] This is a draft
of what I'm working on these days.

142
00:07:15,082 --> 00:07:18,835
It's about a young master and his servant.
I'd appreciate your feedback on this.

143
00:07:21,213 --> 00:07:23,298
[online friend 1]
I love the relationship setting.

144
00:07:23,966 --> 00:07:26,635
[online friend 2] I wonder why
your novels don't get many views.

145
00:07:26,718 --> 00:07:28,345
I feel frustrated myself.

146
00:07:28,971 --> 00:07:32,349
[Eui-ju] A sweet young master bawling
because of a feisty servant.

147
00:07:32,432 --> 00:07:34,851
[sighs] Just thinking about it
is thrilling.

148
00:07:35,936 --> 00:07:37,437
[door creaks]

149
00:07:39,815 --> 00:07:40,857
[music stops]

150
00:07:44,152 --> 00:07:45,153
[Eui-ju] I think

151
00:07:46,029 --> 00:07:47,030
there's someone

152
00:07:47,656 --> 00:07:49,616
behind me right now.

153
00:07:50,701 --> 00:07:51,827
Could it be a ghost?

154
00:07:52,577 --> 00:07:54,413
[online friend 1]
You'll be happy if it's a ghost.

155
00:07:54,496 --> 00:07:56,373
If it's your parents,
my heart goes out to you.

156
00:07:56,456 --> 00:07:58,542
[tense music playing]

157
00:08:06,049 --> 00:08:07,217
[exhales heavily]

158
00:08:11,555 --> 00:08:13,932
-[tapping keys]
-[owl hooting]

159
00:08:16,768 --> 00:08:18,312
[thunder rumbles]

160
00:08:18,395 --> 00:08:19,438
[thunderclap]

161
00:08:23,150 --> 00:08:24,318
Did you see it?

162
00:08:27,446 --> 00:08:30,991
Well, at least,
I'm glad it wasn't my mom or my dad.

163
00:08:31,074 --> 00:08:34,411
But I do have to keep buying him soda
whenever he wants me to.

164
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,830
-[sighs]
-Why do you like it so much?

165
00:08:37,706 --> 00:08:39,207
I don't know.

166
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:40,876
I just like it. That's all.

167
00:08:42,961 --> 00:08:45,005
That's probably why
you're still going at it.

168
00:08:46,173 --> 00:08:48,884
Well, somehow I still feel like
I'll make it big one day.

169
00:08:52,179 --> 00:08:53,597
So you have baseless confidence.

170
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:57,559
If your confidence has a basis,
that's not confidence, it's a prediction.

171
00:08:57,642 --> 00:09:00,645
[gasps] That means
I'm going to keep moving forward.

172
00:09:00,729 --> 00:09:01,980
And I'll keep getting better.

173
00:09:05,859 --> 00:09:07,069
Mr. Ga.

174
00:09:07,152 --> 00:09:12,074
Remember, when EBC came
to film the TV show,

175
00:09:12,157 --> 00:09:15,327
and you stopped
right in the middle of telling your story?

176
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:16,453
[clears throat]

177
00:09:16,536 --> 00:09:19,664
I still want to know why
you decided to become a teacher.

178
00:09:34,304 --> 00:09:36,306
[people talking on television]

179
00:09:37,349 --> 00:09:38,392
So did you have a good time?

180
00:09:39,267 --> 00:09:40,268
Yeah.

181
00:09:41,978 --> 00:09:43,397
[groans]

182
00:09:44,231 --> 00:09:47,859
She came back to Korea after years
of glory for having won a Fields Medal.

183
00:09:47,943 --> 00:09:50,862
But she came all the way to Jeonju
just to see you?

184
00:09:50,946 --> 00:09:52,239
Huh? Why?

185
00:09:52,322 --> 00:09:54,616
And it wasn't like
she wanted to see the whole Olympiad crew.

186
00:09:54,699 --> 00:09:55,700
It was just you.

187
00:09:55,784 --> 00:09:56,993
Only you.

188
00:09:57,077 --> 00:09:58,370
Why only you?

189
00:09:59,204 --> 00:10:02,833
I guess beautiful memories sprouted
from a fragment of your summer-like youth.

190
00:10:03,417 --> 00:10:05,335
-[Gi-jeon] Did they go out together?
-[Da-ju] Mmm!

191
00:10:05,419 --> 00:10:07,295
There really is
no other explanation for it.

192
00:10:07,379 --> 00:10:10,507
For things to be like that,
there has to be chemistry

193
00:10:10,590 --> 00:10:11,758
between a man and a woman.

194
00:10:11,842 --> 00:10:14,219
That spark is
what makes you remember someone

195
00:10:14,302 --> 00:10:16,430
for years
and makes you want to see them again.

196
00:10:16,513 --> 00:10:18,056
-Comprendes, amigo?
-[Gi-jeon] Right.

197
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:19,224
It's none of your business.

198
00:10:21,852 --> 00:10:23,854
-Guess it's true.
-[door closes]

199
00:10:23,937 --> 00:10:26,773
That bastard wasn't just studying
after all. [clicks tongue]

200
00:10:27,816 --> 00:10:32,154
The way I see it, that girl Na Deul-i and
Woo-su met at the Olympiad,

201
00:10:32,237 --> 00:10:34,906
dated, and then they just broke up.

202
00:10:34,990 --> 00:10:36,783
-No way.
-Mm-hmm.

203
00:10:36,867 --> 00:10:39,202
That's why he dropped out
in the middle of it all. Why?

204
00:10:39,286 --> 00:10:41,538
Just to go see his ex-girlfriend again,

205
00:10:42,247 --> 00:10:43,248
his heart…

206
00:10:43,331 --> 00:10:45,041
-Mm-mmm…
-His heart.

207
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:48,420
He felt too restless and uneasy.
That's why he couldn't keep going.

208
00:10:49,254 --> 00:10:53,341
The cold-blooded Ga Woo-su had
a flicker of love.

209
00:10:53,425 --> 00:10:55,469
-[sighs] Dang.
-You know what I'm saying?

210
00:10:55,552 --> 00:10:57,971
-Yeah, that's my boy. [clicks tongue]
-Come on. That can't be the reason.

211
00:10:58,847 --> 00:10:59,848
It sure can be.

212
00:11:00,682 --> 00:11:02,434
Why? Because they were rivals.

213
00:11:03,226 --> 00:11:04,227
Woo-su must've gone, like…

214
00:11:07,147 --> 00:11:08,356
"I'll give up here.

215
00:11:09,065 --> 00:11:10,859
You can go higher or whatever if you want.

216
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:12,611
Only one of us can win."

217
00:11:12,694 --> 00:11:16,656
So you're saying Woo-su gave up
on math over a girl he liked? No way.

218
00:11:18,283 --> 00:11:19,284
Actually,

219
00:11:20,035 --> 00:11:21,036
there's another reason.

220
00:11:22,245 --> 00:11:23,330
What is it?

221
00:11:26,082 --> 00:11:27,083
You know,

222
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:28,668
his camera phobia.

223
00:11:30,086 --> 00:11:31,171
He gave up in case he won.

224
00:11:31,254 --> 00:11:32,631
-Mmm…
-Ah…

225
00:11:33,256 --> 00:11:34,257
[scoffs]

226
00:11:37,511 --> 00:11:39,513
[imitates Deul-i] "Wow.
It's such a surprise

227
00:11:39,596 --> 00:11:41,348
to see that
you have a student of your own.

228
00:11:41,890 --> 00:11:43,099
[scoffs]

229
00:11:43,183 --> 00:11:45,310
[normal voice]
Why is it such a surprise? Huh?

230
00:11:45,393 --> 00:11:47,521
Is it that surprising for a teacher
to have a student?

231
00:11:48,855 --> 00:11:50,607
I'll see you again another time, Eui-ju.

232
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:53,068
"Another time"?

233
00:11:53,902 --> 00:11:54,903
[scoffs]

234
00:11:55,403 --> 00:11:56,404
That's right.

235
00:11:57,781 --> 00:11:59,407
We may meet again sometime.

236
00:12:01,993 --> 00:12:02,994
[clears throat]

237
00:12:03,078 --> 00:12:05,080
-[whimsical music playing]
-[sighs]

238
00:12:09,209 --> 00:12:10,919
[dramatic sting plays]

239
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:17,467
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 7

240
00:12:17,551 --> 00:12:19,844
[Dong-ju coughing]

241
00:12:19,928 --> 00:12:21,930
[suspenseful music playing]

242
00:12:23,181 --> 00:12:25,183
[rope grinding, creaking]

243
00:12:32,482 --> 00:12:33,900
Who are you?

244
00:12:38,655 --> 00:12:39,656
Me?

245
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,950
The Chair's secretary, Na Ran-i.

246
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:46,538
As long as I'm getting paid, I'll do
anything, even dirty work like this.

247
00:12:46,621 --> 00:12:47,789
[sinister music playing]

248
00:12:47,872 --> 00:12:49,916
I was ordered to get you away
from Ju Si-on.

249
00:12:51,084 --> 00:12:53,003
Your face is too handsome to be wasted.

250
00:12:53,086 --> 00:12:54,296
[chuckles]

251
00:12:54,379 --> 00:12:55,672
But I need you gone.

252
00:12:56,339 --> 00:12:58,508
-Don't do it! Don't!
-[grunts]

253
00:12:59,009 --> 00:13:00,427
-[grunts]
-[groans]

254
00:13:02,804 --> 00:13:03,930
[door bangs]

255
00:13:04,014 --> 00:13:05,932
[western music playing]

256
00:13:06,016 --> 00:13:07,934
Choi Yoon!

257
00:13:08,018 --> 00:13:09,936
[gasps] How did you find us?

258
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:11,605
[breathes heavily, grunts]

259
00:13:16,443 --> 00:13:17,777
[grunts]

260
00:13:20,322 --> 00:13:22,073
-[Deul-i grunts]
-[grunts]

261
00:13:22,157 --> 00:13:25,577
[grunting]

262
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:33,793
[yells]

263
00:13:35,003 --> 00:13:36,921
-[grunts]
-[Woo-su grunts]

264
00:13:37,005 --> 00:13:38,256
[groans]

265
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:39,424
[pants]

266
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:42,636
-[Deul-i grunts]
-Choi Yoon!

267
00:13:50,393 --> 00:13:51,394
Are you okay?

268
00:13:54,689 --> 00:13:55,940
Yes, I'm okay.

269
00:13:59,069 --> 00:14:01,279
SI-ON LOWERED HIMSELF
TO MEET YOON'S EYES

270
00:14:01,863 --> 00:14:02,947
Let's go.

271
00:14:05,659 --> 00:14:09,120
SO CLOSE AND SO INTENSE,
HIS GAZE MADE YOON'S HEART RACE

272
00:14:14,584 --> 00:14:16,336
JUST THEN, RAN-I CALLED OUT

273
00:14:16,419 --> 00:14:17,504
[Deul-i] This is amusing.

274
00:14:19,005 --> 00:14:21,216
We'll see how long
you can keep this whole thing going.

275
00:14:21,841 --> 00:14:24,177
RAN-I'S COMMENT
PROVOKED YOON'S WILDER NATURE

276
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:25,261
Hold on.

277
00:14:26,179 --> 00:14:28,014
I don't leave debts unpaid.

278
00:14:29,099 --> 00:14:30,392
[Deul-i] No!

279
00:14:30,475 --> 00:14:32,268
No! Don't do it!

280
00:14:33,937 --> 00:14:35,563
YOON BID HER FAREWELL

281
00:14:35,647 --> 00:14:39,943
IT WAS FOR SI-ON, OF ALL PEOPLE

282
00:14:45,156 --> 00:14:47,075
[sighs]

283
00:14:47,158 --> 00:14:50,328
CHAPTER 33:
SOMETHING UTTERLY USELESS

284
00:14:51,413 --> 00:14:52,872
-[Woo-su] Eun Ha-su.
-Here.

285
00:14:53,748 --> 00:14:54,999
-[Woo-su] Oh A-rin.
-Here.

286
00:14:55,709 --> 00:14:56,876
-[Woo-su] Choi Yu-mi.
-Here.

287
00:14:57,961 --> 00:14:59,546
-[Woo-su] Yeo Eui-ju.
-Here.

288
00:15:00,130 --> 00:15:02,173
-Choi Go-ya.
-Here.

289
00:15:02,257 --> 00:15:03,425
Choi Ji-a.

290
00:15:07,554 --> 00:15:08,722
-Hong Su-min.
-Here.

291
00:15:08,805 --> 00:15:10,765
-[Woo-su] Jeon Chae-won.
-Here.

292
00:15:10,849 --> 00:15:12,642
-[Woo-su] Im Su-yeon.
-Here.

293
00:15:22,152 --> 00:15:23,528
-Im Su-yeon.
-Here.

294
00:15:23,611 --> 00:15:25,280
-[Woo-su] Lee Eun-ji.
-Here.

295
00:15:25,363 --> 00:15:26,614
-[Woo-su] Choi Hye-jeong.
-Here.

296
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:29,701
Are you ready for today's class?

297
00:15:29,784 --> 00:15:31,911
[students murmuring]

298
00:15:31,995 --> 00:15:33,788
Why does it smell like alcohol?

299
00:15:33,872 --> 00:15:34,873
Do you smell that?

300
00:15:34,956 --> 00:15:36,332
-[tense music playing]
-It smells so nasty.

301
00:15:36,416 --> 00:15:37,667
It kinda smells like alcohol.

302
00:15:43,047 --> 00:15:45,049
-[pounds]
-Quiet down.

303
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:49,512
Who is on cleaning duty?

304
00:15:50,388 --> 00:15:51,556
[Eui-ju] M-Me.

305
00:15:53,099 --> 00:15:54,434
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Yes?

306
00:15:55,018 --> 00:15:56,853
-Do it again.
-Sure.

307
00:15:56,936 --> 00:15:59,063
Let some air in. Open the windows.

308
00:15:59,147 --> 00:16:01,232
-[students murmuring]
-[student grunts] It's cold.

309
00:16:01,316 --> 00:16:02,609
Why? Is he for real?

310
00:16:03,401 --> 00:16:05,069
Choi Ji-a, go see the nurse.

311
00:16:05,945 --> 00:16:08,948
[students whispering]

312
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:25,298
-Hi.
-Hello.

313
00:16:26,341 --> 00:16:27,801
[sniffing]

314
00:16:31,888 --> 00:16:32,889
Hey!

315
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:45,068
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

316
00:16:45,151 --> 00:16:47,111
She's your student, right?

317
00:16:47,195 --> 00:16:50,323
Are you aware that
she came to school completely drunk?

318
00:16:50,406 --> 00:16:52,784
[Young-hee] Outrageous!
Totally outrageous.

319
00:16:52,867 --> 00:16:56,538
How could a student come to school
reeking of alcohol like this, huh?

320
00:16:58,164 --> 00:16:59,290
[retches]

321
00:16:59,374 --> 00:17:01,000
[E-den, Young-hee scoff]

322
00:17:01,709 --> 00:17:04,045
Aren't you the one
who didn't wear a school uniform

323
00:17:04,128 --> 00:17:05,463
during the EBC production?

324
00:17:05,547 --> 00:17:08,675
Do you even plan
to keep going to school at all, dear?

325
00:17:08,758 --> 00:17:09,801
Please, Ms. Kim.

326
00:17:10,552 --> 00:17:13,721
Let me talk to her and find out exactly
what happened, and I'll get back to you.

327
00:17:14,848 --> 00:17:16,015
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

328
00:17:16,099 --> 00:17:20,854
Is there any reason whatsoever
I should tolerate underage drinking here?

329
00:17:24,065 --> 00:17:25,233
Wait outside.

330
00:17:30,572 --> 00:17:32,615
-[tuts]
-[door closes]

331
00:17:32,699 --> 00:17:35,493
I don't wanna argue
over something trivial.

332
00:17:35,577 --> 00:17:36,870
[groans]

333
00:17:36,953 --> 00:17:38,371
I got a massage yesterday.

334
00:17:38,454 --> 00:17:39,956
-[E-den] Aw…
-My shoulders are stiff again.

335
00:17:40,039 --> 00:17:41,040
[groans]

336
00:17:41,624 --> 00:17:45,461
Choi Ji-a has different circumstances
from those of other students.

337
00:17:45,545 --> 00:17:48,214
Without parental care,
she lives in a foster shelter,

338
00:17:48,298 --> 00:17:49,757
working to support herself.

339
00:17:49,841 --> 00:17:53,386
Even after all that, she's still willing
to come to school almost every day.

340
00:17:53,469 --> 00:17:55,346
Oh, really?

341
00:17:55,430 --> 00:17:56,764
That's great.

342
00:17:56,848 --> 00:17:59,767
She'll be able to manage
at another school then. Hmm?

343
00:17:59,851 --> 00:18:02,186
She might look tough
but she's still just a kid.

344
00:18:04,355 --> 00:18:07,025
As her homeroom teacher,
I'll take responsibility

345
00:18:07,609 --> 00:18:09,944
and I'll make sure
you see real change in Choi Ji-a.

346
00:18:10,987 --> 00:18:12,196
Please just give her chance.

347
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:13,573
Mr. Ga Woo-su.

348
00:18:13,656 --> 00:18:15,575
Do you know what our school motto is?

349
00:18:16,326 --> 00:18:19,245
Be an Elite! That's what it is.

350
00:18:19,954 --> 00:18:23,458
No matter how you look at it, whatever
that student plans to do with her life…

351
00:18:23,541 --> 00:18:25,418
[sighs] …it's a far cry from that.

352
00:18:26,085 --> 00:18:27,962
And no matter how much I think of it,

353
00:18:28,463 --> 00:18:32,133
she just doesn't belong
at Murim Girls' High School. That's all.

354
00:18:32,216 --> 00:18:34,260
You may go now.

355
00:18:35,261 --> 00:18:36,763
[sighs]

356
00:18:42,769 --> 00:18:44,270
-[door closes]
-[E-den scoffs]

357
00:18:44,354 --> 00:18:47,106
Who does he think he is,
taking the wrong side?

358
00:18:47,190 --> 00:18:50,652
How could he possibly stand up for a kid
who came to school drunk?

359
00:18:50,735 --> 00:18:52,362
[scoffs] So annoying.

360
00:18:53,529 --> 00:18:56,240
Would you believe
he's friends with the Na Deul-i?

361
00:18:56,324 --> 00:18:57,825
Who's Na Deul-i?

362
00:18:57,909 --> 00:19:00,078
Auntie, really? You're kidding.

363
00:19:00,161 --> 00:19:02,038
She's the professor
who won the Fields Medal.

364
00:19:02,121 --> 00:19:03,331
They're friends.

365
00:19:04,082 --> 00:19:05,124
What?

366
00:19:05,625 --> 00:19:08,086
I can't believe what you're saying!

367
00:19:08,169 --> 00:19:10,171
Why are you telling me this now?

368
00:19:10,254 --> 00:19:11,881
When was I supposed to tell you?

369
00:19:12,507 --> 00:19:13,758
-[scoffs]
-[Young-hee exclaims]

370
00:19:18,012 --> 00:19:19,013
Choi Ji-a.

371
00:19:22,934 --> 00:19:24,352
Why did you…

372
00:19:26,187 --> 00:19:28,439
It's wrong for a student
to show up drunk at school.

373
00:19:31,442 --> 00:19:33,945
What matters here is
what you choose to do next.

374
00:19:34,028 --> 00:19:37,240
Write a detailed paper self-reflecting
on what exactly you did wrong

375
00:19:37,323 --> 00:19:38,866
and how you're going to change.

376
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:40,785
I'm going to hand it to the principal.

377
00:19:42,245 --> 00:19:43,871
Okay.

378
00:19:43,955 --> 00:19:47,291
I'll try to reduce the penalty, so
don't forget to wear your school uniform.

379
00:19:48,418 --> 00:19:50,336
And no more absences.

380
00:19:50,420 --> 00:19:51,921
Okay.

381
00:19:57,427 --> 00:19:59,303
-[Yeong-jae] This is the best.
-[Dan-ji] What on earth is this?

382
00:19:59,387 --> 00:20:01,097
-Hey, Eui-ju. Over here. Come on.
-Eui-ju, come!

383
00:20:01,180 --> 00:20:02,807
-Hurry. Over here.
-That was so cool.

384
00:20:02,890 --> 00:20:05,184
-Whoa, this is to die for.
-Try this.

385
00:20:05,268 --> 00:20:06,602
This lunch is so delicious.

386
00:20:06,686 --> 00:20:08,021
Go-ya, where are you going?

387
00:20:09,731 --> 00:20:10,815
Can I eat here with you?

388
00:20:12,400 --> 00:20:13,735
Eui-ju, sit down. Sit.

389
00:20:13,818 --> 00:20:14,944
[Dan-ji] Let's…

390
00:20:15,028 --> 00:20:16,529
[student] Here. Have some of my soup.

391
00:20:17,530 --> 00:20:20,491
[Yeong-jae] Oh. The meat is
so delicious today. Try this too.

392
00:20:20,575 --> 00:20:22,368
Eat up, Eui-ju. It's so good.

393
00:20:26,205 --> 00:20:28,249
Go-ya, can I talk to you for a sec…

394
00:20:28,332 --> 00:20:29,834
[student] I don't know.
I left them in my locker.

395
00:20:29,917 --> 00:20:31,794
[student 2] Yeah. The exam is coming soon.

396
00:20:32,503 --> 00:20:33,504
Where are you going? Huh?

397
00:20:33,588 --> 00:20:34,797
No, I get it.

398
00:20:34,881 --> 00:20:37,008
-Guys, guys I have crazy news.
-What is it?

399
00:20:37,091 --> 00:20:39,385
Guess what.
Young-hee was going to transfer Ji-a.

400
00:20:39,469 --> 00:20:41,179
But Mr. Ga stopped her.

401
00:20:41,763 --> 00:20:42,764
-Really?
-No way.

402
00:20:42,847 --> 00:20:44,140
She's on probation.

403
00:20:45,016 --> 00:20:48,269
Hmm. I wonder what kind of card he played.

404
00:20:48,936 --> 00:20:50,021
I bet there's something.

405
00:20:52,065 --> 00:20:54,442
Anyway, when are you going
to make up with Go-ya?

406
00:20:54,525 --> 00:20:57,403
You keep making me
tell the same story twice. [smacks lips]

407
00:20:57,487 --> 00:20:58,488
What a mess, huh?

408
00:20:58,571 --> 00:20:59,822
Um…

409
00:20:59,906 --> 00:21:02,867
Does she still refuse to talk to you?

410
00:21:03,951 --> 00:21:04,952
Mm-hmm.

411
00:21:05,453 --> 00:21:08,915
Well then what did you guys fight about?

412
00:21:11,834 --> 00:21:12,960
We didn't.

413
00:21:13,044 --> 00:21:14,754
W-We didn't fight.

414
00:21:15,713 --> 00:21:16,839
-[Dan-ji] What is it?
-[Yeong-jae] As if.

415
00:21:16,923 --> 00:21:19,008
-[Dan-ji] Come on. Tell us.
-I don't believe you.

416
00:21:20,384 --> 00:21:22,720
[crickets chirping]

417
00:21:27,892 --> 00:21:30,103
[Deul-i] I'm looking to do
some joint research with you.

418
00:21:30,186 --> 00:21:31,979
[gentle music playing]

419
00:21:33,147 --> 00:21:35,733
It's been really nice talking to you.

420
00:21:37,110 --> 00:21:38,236
[chuckles]

421
00:21:38,319 --> 00:21:39,862
I'm not sure how long it will take

422
00:21:39,946 --> 00:21:41,906
but I'd really like to study it with you.

423
00:21:42,573 --> 00:21:44,992
The topology of algebraic curves
and surfaces.

424
00:21:48,955 --> 00:21:49,956
Why that topic?

425
00:21:51,415 --> 00:21:53,918
I don't know. I was just drawn to it.

426
00:21:54,418 --> 00:21:56,671
When looking for something that
is never useful.

427
00:22:00,049 --> 00:22:04,262
It reminded me of a quote
by the British mathematician Hardy.

428
00:22:04,345 --> 00:22:06,681
"None of my discoveries has made,

429
00:22:06,764 --> 00:22:08,307
or is likely to make,

430
00:22:08,391 --> 00:22:11,018
any difference
to the comfort of the world,

431
00:22:11,102 --> 00:22:12,979
directly or indirectly.

432
00:22:13,062 --> 00:22:14,772
-For better or worse…
-"…or worse,

433
00:22:14,856 --> 00:22:17,191
[both] I have never done anything useful."

434
00:22:19,610 --> 00:22:21,821
[both chuckle]

435
00:22:22,530 --> 00:22:23,948
I want to try that.

436
00:22:24,615 --> 00:22:26,617
Accomplishing something utterly useless.

437
00:22:32,748 --> 00:22:33,749
[sighs]

438
00:22:43,801 --> 00:22:45,052
Where are you going?

439
00:22:45,136 --> 00:22:46,470
For a walk.

440
00:22:46,554 --> 00:22:48,890
I'll come with.
I need to go for a walk too.

441
00:22:51,517 --> 00:22:53,060
Are you still getting headaches?

442
00:22:53,144 --> 00:22:54,145
Sometimes.

443
00:22:54,729 --> 00:22:56,189
Shouldn't you see the doctor?

444
00:22:56,272 --> 00:22:57,315
It's not that bad.

445
00:22:57,982 --> 00:22:59,734
[Dong-ju] Still, go for a checkup.

446
00:22:59,817 --> 00:23:01,485
It's better to be safe than sorry.

447
00:23:02,028 --> 00:23:03,029
[Woo-su] Okay.

448
00:23:03,571 --> 00:23:05,198
[Dong-ju] Don't just say it, though.

449
00:23:05,281 --> 00:23:06,282
Make sure you go.

450
00:23:07,408 --> 00:23:08,409
[Woo-su] Okay.

451
00:23:10,995 --> 00:23:11,996
[sighs]

452
00:23:13,497 --> 00:23:15,917
[smacks lips, sighs]

453
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,001
[laptop chimes]

454
00:23:20,087 --> 00:23:21,255
I need a soda.

455
00:23:22,506 --> 00:23:23,883
[sighs]

456
00:23:23,966 --> 00:23:26,844
But I'm already home!

457
00:23:28,054 --> 00:23:30,223
-[sighs]
-[typing]

458
00:23:30,306 --> 00:23:31,724
I'm in my room already.

459
00:23:31,807 --> 00:23:33,267
Can't you wait until tomorrow?

460
00:23:35,353 --> 00:23:37,980
Mom! I have something to tell you.

461
00:23:38,064 --> 00:23:39,482
Hey, hey, hey, Eui-do.

462
00:23:39,565 --> 00:23:41,192
Okay, fine. [laughs] Okay, fine.

463
00:23:41,275 --> 00:23:42,276
I'll go, I'll go.

464
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,569
[sighs]

465
00:23:43,653 --> 00:23:45,655
[pop music playing on speakers]

466
00:24:03,089 --> 00:24:04,840
What do you think
about your friend's offer?

467
00:24:05,591 --> 00:24:06,592
Na Deul-i's?

468
00:24:07,343 --> 00:24:08,344
Honestly.

469
00:24:08,844 --> 00:24:10,680
Not interested at all.

470
00:24:11,514 --> 00:24:12,515
That's a lie.

471
00:24:13,432 --> 00:24:16,143
You answered that way too fast.
Like it was planned.

472
00:24:17,979 --> 00:24:21,691
You know, I want you to spend your time
on something that you really want to do.

473
00:24:22,984 --> 00:24:25,194
So when you have a chance,
go to the States.

474
00:24:25,278 --> 00:24:26,570
And do the research you want

475
00:24:27,446 --> 00:24:28,447
before it's too late.

476
00:24:29,824 --> 00:24:31,575
[Eui-ju] You're going to the States,
Mr. Ga?

477
00:24:34,662 --> 00:24:37,873
[somber music playing]

478
00:25:08,988 --> 00:25:11,324
-[Woo-su] It's late. Go home.
-No.

479
00:25:11,407 --> 00:25:13,284
The truth is, I…

480
00:25:13,367 --> 00:25:15,202
[Woo-su] Didn't I tell you
to stay away from her?

481
00:25:15,286 --> 00:25:16,996
[Dong-ju groans] Now what?

482
00:25:17,079 --> 00:25:19,415
-[Woo-su] How did you get here?
-[Eui-ju] Mr. Ga. What do I do?

483
00:25:19,498 --> 00:25:22,543
[grunts] Why wouldn't she pick up?
Why is she not even checking her phone?

484
00:25:22,626 --> 00:25:24,837
-[Ji-a] Get out of here.
-[gasps] Mr. Ga!

485
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:26,714
[Woo-su] I guess
you guys haven't figured me out yet.

486
00:25:26,797 --> 00:25:29,008
[Eui-ju] You'll be dead meat
for real, then.

487
00:25:29,091 --> 00:25:31,385
Dang. He's so cool.

488
00:25:31,469 --> 00:25:33,012
So cool.

489
00:25:33,095 --> 00:25:34,263
[Go-ya] Just tell him.

490
00:25:34,347 --> 00:25:36,724
You have to look into his eyes
to show you mean it.

491
00:25:36,807 --> 00:25:38,476
-I…
-[Go-ya] Make eye contact.

492
00:25:38,559 --> 00:25:40,102
For at least three seconds.

